In this article, it is reported that President Obama spoke with Chancellor Merkel of Germany regarding allegations that the U.S. National Security Agency intercepted her communications. The President reassured Chancellor Merkel that the United States is not and will not monitor her communications. The article also mentions that the United States values its cooperation with Germany on security issues and that they are reviewing their intelligence gathering practices to balance security concerns with privacy concerns. Both leaders agreed to increase cooperation between their intelligence services to protect the security and privacy of their citizens.